  "instructions": [
    "Season the lamb shoulder with salt and black pepper.",
    "Place the lamb in a salt-block vessel or a clay pot with a heavy lid.",
    "Add shiitake mushrooms, daikon radish, gobo, shoga, sake, soy sauce, mirin, and sugar to the vessel.",
    "Add 1 cup of water to the vessel and place the binchotan-charcoal on top for a smoky flavor.",
    "Cover the vessel and slow cook at 120°C for 4-6 hours or overnight.",
    "Remove the lamb from the vessel and let it rest for 10 minutes before slicing.",
    "Strain the cooking liquid and serve the lamb with the strained sauce.",
    "Serve hot and garnish with toasted sesame seeds and chopped scallions, if desired."
  ],
